Chapter 4: The Neuroadaptive Mars Integration Protocol (N-MIP)

4.1 Core Philosophy: The Martian Cognition Principle

The N-MIP begins with a radical premise: on Mars, human cognition must extend beyond biological limits. The suit is not merely protective gear; it is a cognitive prosthesis. Thought triggers environmental adaptation, and environmental feedback reshapes neural patterns, creating a continuous loop of adaptation that produces Martian‑native intuition.

