The adaptation loss function incorporates environmental anchors:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{total}} = \mathcal{L}_{\text{DAE}} + \mu_1 \mathcal{L}_{\text{neural anchor}} + \mu_2 \mathcal{L}_{\text{environmental anchor}},

with \mathcal{L}_{\text{environmental anchor}} = \| \text{MAS\_state}(t) - \text{MAS\_state}(\text{ref}) \|^2.

