Instead of reacting to conscious intent, the system detects preconscious neural precursors (e.g., in the supplementary motor area) and pre‑activates suit subsystems, saving 80–120 ms—critical for Mars terrain navigation.

A shared predictive model synchronizes the brain's forward model with the MAS's physics engine, testing predicted outcomes against both neural expectations and physical constraints.

