7.4 Integrated Memory: Hybrid RRAM/FeRAM

· RRAM (resistive RAM): Non‑volatile storage of synaptic weights. Retention 10 years at 85 °C, endurance 10⁶ writes (sufficient for daily updates over 15 years). ECC protects against SEUs.
· FeRAM (ferroelectric RAM): Fast, low‑power storage for temporary states (membrane potentials, refractory counters). Endurance 10¹² cycles.

